M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Gross vs. net revenue clearly labeled
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Revenue growth rate > cost growth rate
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] ARPU/ARPA tracked by cohort (not just blended)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Revenue concentration: Top customer <10%, Top 10 <40%
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Monthly churn <5% (ideally <2%)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Revenue churn vs. logo churn compared
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] NRR >100% (ideally >120%)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Quick Ratio >2 (ideally >4)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Recent cohorts perform same or better than older cohorts
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Revenue retention tracked, not just logo retention
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Expansion analyzed by cohort
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|Check if any of these apply:
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Revenue churn > logo churn (losing big customers)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] ARPU growing but customer count shrinking (mix shift, not improvement)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Newer cohorts churn faster than older cohorts (PMF degradation)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] NRR <100% (contracting, not expanding)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Quick Ratio <2 (leaky bucket)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Discounts >20% or refunds >10% (pricing/product problems)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Revenue concentration >50% in top 10 customers (risk)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|- [ ] Expansion revenue <10% of total MRR (monetization problem)
M|saas-revenue-growth-metrics|**If you checked any red flags, see SKILL.md Common Pitfalls section for fixes.**